issue.title: Quickstart examples throws error: (given 1, expected 0) (ArgumentError)

labels.name: type: bug
labels.description: Error or flaw in code with unintended results or allowing sub-optimal usage patterns.

labels.name: priority: p2
labels.description: Moderately-important priority. Fix may not be included in next release.

issue.body:
Thanks for stopping by to let us know something could be better!

Please run down the following list and make sure you've tried the usual "quick fixes":

  - Search the issues already opened: https://github.com/googleapis/google-cloud-ruby/issues
  - Search StackOverflow: http://stackoverflow.com/questions/tagged/google-cloud-platform+ruby

If you are still having issues, please be sure to include as much information as possible:

#### Environment details

  - OS: Mac OS Ventura
  - Ruby version: 3.2.1
  - Gem name and version:  `"google-cloud-firestore", "~> 0.21.1"`

#### Steps to reproduce

I'm following the quickstart example here in the docs https://firebase.google.com/docs/firestore/quickstart#ruby

Run the following code in `bin/rails console`
```
irb(main):003:0> Fuego.new
```

#### Code example
I'm using sorbet

```
# typed: strict
# frozen_string_literal: true

require "google/cloud/firestore"

class Fuego
  extend T::Sig

  sig { void }
  def initialize
    ENV["GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS"] = Rails.root.join("config/credentials/gcloud-key.json").to_s

    firestore = Google::Cloud::Firestore.new(project_id: "my-project")
    collection_path = "users"

    doc_ref = firestore.doc("#{collection_path}/alovelace")

    doc_ref.set(
      {
        first: "Ada",
        last: "Lovelace",
        born: 1815,
      },
    )
  end
end
```

#### Full backtrace

```sh
irb(main):003:0> Fuego.new
/Users/tyler/.rbenv/versions/3.2.1/lib/ruby/gems/3.2.0/gems/google-gax-1.8.2/lib/google/gax/settings.rb:171:in `initialize': wrong number of arguments (given 1, expected 0) (ArgumentError)
```

#### Context
It seems like this could be related to this issue https://github.com/googleapis/google-cloud-ruby/issues/8580

issue.title: BigQuery: Add support dataset's storageBillingModel

labels.name: api: bigquery
labels.description: Issues related to the BigQuery API.

issue.body:
Dataset does not support to set or change storageBillingModel.
StorageBillingModel is important to save storage cost.
ref: https://cloud.google.com/bigquery/docs/reference/rest/v2/datasets

comment.body:
It can be set as shown in the code below.

 ```ruby
  bigquery.create_dataset "dataset_id" do |dataset|
     dataset.gapi.storage_billing_model= "LOGICAL"
  end
```
